<TITLE> Warid to distribute 12,000 bags among under-privileged school goers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept. 8 (bdnews24.com) - Warid, a subsidiary of the UAE-based business giant Abu Dhabi Group, Tuesday said that it would distribute 12,000 school bags to the under-privileged children to demonstrate its corporate social responsibility immediately after Eid. Warid chief executive officer Muneer Farooqui announced the plan at Dhaka Sheraton, saying that his company wants to work to help the government in implementing education for all scheme. Farooqui said they have made the bags with used materials of the company billboards under a special "Waste to Asset: scheme. He said maintaining an environment-friendly atmosphere is the call of time, and they have gone by the philosophy of 3Rs of waste management: Reduce, Reuse and Recycle. He said he believed this small initiative would "go a long way" to serve the cause of education for all campaign in the country. b
